<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section 11507 requires a master of a vessel of the United States to surrender to the proper authorities any officer who has violated <ref href="/us/usc/t18/s2191">section 2191 of title 18</ref> (which provides a penalty for cruelty to seamen by officers), and penalizes the master for noncompliance.</p>
</note>
